# Git Rules

Protect user work and keep repository history understandable.

## Safety

- Check working tree status before broad edits.
- Do not revert user changes unless explicitly requested.
- Do not delete generated or user files as cleanup unless the user asks.
- Never commit secrets or local-only files.

## Ignore Policy

- Keep generated build output ignored.
- Keep dependency folders ignored.
- Keep local Obsidian workspace state ignored.
- Keep local AI/editor cache and logs ignored.

## Change Hygiene

- Keep changes scoped to the request.
- Separate structural rule updates from product implementation when practical.
- Summarize changed files and why they changed.
